sentences: Sai kuulsaks, aga ennast täis ei läinud.
Euroopal on iseenesest küll, ta on otse ääreni iseennast täis.
context: Iseennast is an Estonian adjective phrase that describes someone who has too high an opinion of themselves, being conceited or arrogant. It literally means 'full of oneself' and is often used in the construction 'ennast täis' (full of oneself) to criticize people who are overly proud or self-important.
